column6: ["recently we went mostly n capable in our home so i needed an n router and narrowed it down to this choice i wish i hadn't we have 2 imac aluminum models in our house two n capable notebooks and some g products ipod touch g wifi stereo g wifi psp etc etc for all the <OOV> stuff we needed for computers 100 n except for the router i've bought this one and now i've been through two of these units and they both exhibited the same problem the belkin will lose the dns settings being fed to it by", "it took an hour on the phone with belkin support to get my new router working with my mac the person i spoke to was anxious to help but clearly clueless about macs and had to keep asking someone else for assistance once installed the router is blazing fast however i have to unplug it before i put my mac in sleep mode otherwise it will freeze my mac so it seems not exactly 100 compatible but i don't mind doing that one thing every night friends who use mac have told me they find this router incompatible with mac", "replacing my linksys was not in question since even though it was highly rated it locked up and required a restart at inconvenient and odd intervals the linksys modem was working good so i kept that and went looking for a more stable router i chose the belkin based on reviews here and other websites and got the mimo version since we have a powerbook a desktop pc and an older laptop i prefer to get the router up and running then go back and set security going through the basic cd setup was a breeze but the belkin wouldn't", 'it was a little difficult to set up but after it was all done it worked like it was supposed to', 'i switched from sbc to comcast internet and had issues making more than 1 mac computer work at a time with the comcast cable modem and a time capsule i purchased one of these routers and within 15 minutes had two laptops my imac and a network printer up and running perfectly the router and install cd are mac os friendly and the wireless feature security works very well using os 10 5 imac intel macbook pro and ibook <OOV> value for the price', 'should have spent a little more for the netgear router that i knew worked but the belkin n router looked nice and <OOV> out well problem with running ubuntu is that the setup cd doesnt work usually they dont and you just setup through the browser but after doing that it still sucked so i am guessing there is something in the windoze version that i didnt see while running linux that makes it work that or it is just garbage weird but the wifi worked well it was the hard wired lan that didnt oh well bye bye belkin', 'our house is a single story of about 1000 square feet and we have had no problems with this modem the only issues we have experienced with connectivity have been because of the internet provider not the modem i will buy another belkin router if this one ever dies', "this is the best wireless router i've had any problems we may have had with it we called the company and no matter how long it took they got us working it was not the product it was our human error once this router was hooked up properly the ease of loading the software and it started right up everything wireless is now hooked up and it's truly wonderful i've definitely recommended it to family and friends the price i got it for was <OOV> well worth the buy since i've been hooked up i have not had a problem"]

column6: ['i brought this on a whim for my macbook and i could not be happier it went on quick and painless and looks great i have had no problems with the full range of motion of the screen like others have mentioned this also helps a lot with the scratching that the macbook does on your wrists if you type like i do overall a good product and i am happy with the results only downfall is that it does not show the apple in the back but i guess u cant have everything', 'this is a real <OOV> for me every morning i would waste 10 minutes searching for my stupid zippered neoprene cover i use my computer everywhere in the house and trying to locate where i last set the neoprene cover down was a real hassle for me i also open close my macbook repeatedly as i move around between classes when class is over i normally have to take out the zippered cover place my computer in it zip it back up then load in my backpack this may not seem like an extra effort but in a large classroom', "the shell is definitely a worthwhile investment i've received numerous compliments regarding its appearance and how it helps to personalize our work issued computers i purchased this specific shell because it was on sale for half off making it somewhat affordable whereas the other shells were forty and fifty dollars a piece first off i think that's entirely too much to ask for these things no matter what they're made of but secondly i was not about to pay that much to purchase a shell for a computer that wasn't even mine i'm a school teacher and it's my <OOV>", 'it does a good enough job at protecting my macbook but after awhile my battery pack became warped i think that it was due to the fact that the case made my macbook very warm and the warm air had nowhere to go', 'this prodcut is even better than described it was so easy to put on and i am <OOV> that it will continue to protect my laptop and it arrived here in two days', "this is the second one of these i have purchased this one for a gift it fits perfectly on a macbook 13 inch and looks great great leather texture and that's about it just a great cover", "it has a critical problem typical security lock for a laptop doesn't fit into a hole because the protection shell doesn't provide enough space for a lock instead you can only see the hole so if you need a security lock do not buy this if you don't mind you may want to try", "i bought this as this was the only mac protection available in a more <OOV> range but to my total surprise i found it to be perfect it doesn't heat my mac more than it used to i use my mac a lot practically the whole day and this is the best thing that would prevent it from scratches due to improper handling it fits perfectly and looks good too i would certainly recommend this product a great value for its price"]

column6: ["we love our hd radio such sound quality such options i'm glad we have it now i just want another one with a port for my ipod then i'll buy another one", "my sweet wife got me this radio for christmas at my request it is a great little unit that i use in my office we've got two npr stations in salt lake city one broadcasts in hd the other does not i can definitely hear the difference when listening to the hd broadcast i also like the multiple feed aspect of the hd signal i don't want to argue with those who like to bash hd radio i can only speak to my personal experience with this unit and the hd signal i get in my city i am using", 'in general the radio works well but it has a fatal flaw there is no battery or other backup for loss of power this makes the radio wakeup alarm useless and the programming of presets a frustrating <OOV> in an age of gigabyte memory sticks this is an unacceptable <OOV>', 'i bought mine as a floor demo model for around 100 i live in an urban neighborhood with a lot of good hd radio options in my city the <OOV> <OOV> is located on the second floor of my house the good the tuner gets decent hd reception with the antenna fully deployed the included antenna is about 6 feet long i was delighted to find many hd stations in my area and many of them have some really nice programming the remote is functional and easy to operate at low and moderate volumes the sound is rich for the', 'sony <OOV> <OOV> hd <OOV> are very pleased with this radio we were a little skeptical because the lower price was not one usually associated with the sony brand when our radio was delivered the box was left on the porch where someone stole the radio and left the box and packing material behind amazon com promptly replaced it without hesitating that is service that is impossible to beat', "this is a great product i live in seattle and we have two npr stations normally i can only receive one of these stations because i am too close to the transmitter that broadcasts one station's signal while stepping all over the other this radio allows me to receive both stations in hd they come in crystal clear as a bonus the stations broadcast multiple hd signals so i essentially now have 5 npr signals to choose from vs only one in the past there are tons of other hd stations that are being broadcasted in this area i especially", "i love this radio it's a great sounding table radio with a small footprint i've been switching between the hd stations and playing lp's using the line in feature with an external phono preamp and the results are very listenable beats my bose 321 for sound quality", "i needed a table top radio for my new office i did a fair amount of research but was frustrated with the <OOV> of reviews zilch on cnet etc i did a test drive of a demo unit at a store and it sounded ok and the hd aspect seemed to work i ordered a unit and have had it for about a week no problems with the reception i am now able to pick up the local npr fm station along with its two additional digital bands i listen at low volumes at work so i generally don't crank"]

column6: ['i bought this tv 2 years ago based on reviews that stated it was better than lcd or plasma i have to say that it is still incredible aside from the wider viewing angle you get from lcd and plasma and the fact that you cant hang it on a wall i cant see any advantage to lcd or plasma that is worth the price difference also i like the fact that its qam tuner allows me to get lots of hd channels that i have not paid for since i only have a basic cable package perhaps that will', "great tv had it about 6 weeks now and couldn't be happier with it a little history i looked for the ideal plasma lcd set in my price range for several months working out the pros cons and trade offs between the various sets and waiting for substantial price drops i had seen this tv playing in several electronic stores but was never impressed one day i stopped in a store that had one connected to a blu ray player and was calibrated i was stunned by the performance the only other tv in the store that came close to", "i did a lot of research before deciding to purchase this tv i am so glad that i did both the research and buying the sony first you have to go out to your local brick and mortar stores and look at all of the tv's with your eye when you do you'll see like i did that the sony just looks better the main competitor that i considered for the sony was the dlp it's the mirrors brand when you go look at them though it is silly how much better the sony is sony bravia at 120 hz", "the tv is awesome i upgraded from a 50 nec plasma that had reached the end of its life here's the best part the sony sits on the same stand i had the nec on though it's several inches thicker unless you plan to hang it on a wall there's functionally little difference in terms of size it weighs significantly less than the plasma and the picture is superb far better in my opinion only downside is it takes perhaps 10 15 seconds to warm up i love that the bulb is replaceable unlike my plasma when it died it", 'i am blown away by the tv i have friends with other current rear projection tvs and this is by far a superior picture lots of settings for varying viewing content etc love it', "after much research i purchased the sony kds <OOV> 60 hdtv from amazon i'd purchased many items from amazon over the years but certainly nothing as electronically elaborate and as large as a 60 hdtv first the tv itself is absolutely wonderful i'm 5 pleased about that that would be most important i also must add that i'm also 5 pleased regarding the decision the purchase from amazon the price was terrific i saved 300 on the purchase price and the lack of sales tax saved another almost 200 also via the amazon where's my stuff function i was able", 'i have owned this tv for a little more than a week i spent months researching and agonizing over which brand and type dlp lcd plasma ect of tv to get decided to get this sony over the samsung led first off the set is fantastic much better put together than the samsung cheap and flimsy plastic as far as the picture it is great in hd and very watchable in regular standard def the only problem is although picture is great in hd i am not totally wowed by the picture probably have to tweak the settings some more', 'i was extremely pleased with sony tv bravia 60 hdtv i was initially skeptical that something may go wrong with the online purchase however i was very surprised with the whole experience and saved too in shipping and taxes']

amazing it takes great photos and the 3 5 widescreen touchscreen is very fun and functional at the same time let the <OOV> begin i have had no problems selecting options and such with the touchscreen with my finger or the little stylus attachment that comes with the camera that attaches to the <OOV> i was very impressed with the slideshow mode which has different style and music options for you to choose e g the nostalgia mode plays photos in sepia <OOV> and has slower music slideshows also look great when you connect the camera to', "the first thing you'll notice about this camera is its size definitely the smallest digital camera i've ever seen at the same time the lcd touchscreen on the back is quite large the memory cards i ordered didn't fit sony has a proprietary micro memory card know it will break as soon as you use it on a trip and take the unit off the bike daily', "i am pleased with the product as it is exactly as described the pros are it's rugged and holds the nuvi securely the only con is it's bulky for a bicycle but that shouldn't deter anyone who wants a dependable mount", 'based on the reviews read here i ordered it last week and it arrived today really easy to install instructions included and the nuvi held securely in place worth the money given that i can extend the use of my nuvi beyond the vehicle and can track my pace and distance on the bike path', "if you are looking for ways to have gps convenience while biking and don't want to buy an expensive bicycle gps unit but you already have a garmin unit for your car then this is your baby has rubber pieces that keep your bike scratch free and strong zip ties to secure it the main piece detaches for days you don't want to bring your garmin overall an excellent product", "this handlebar mount only works with the nuvi 200 series after 600 miles of riding the unit stayed put and never came out once so it's definitely a secure mount however in order to prevent it from rotating on your handlebar mount you should put some type of rubber material between the unit and handlebar the only improvement i would make is that the extension of the unit from the handlebar is a bit longer than i'd like", "i bought this for my son before he moved to california the gps been a life saver for him on more than one occasion and since his sole source of transportation is a <OOV> motorcycle this was absolutely necessary it works great it holds the garmin steady over bumps and everything else and he can see the garmin screen it doesn't rain much where he is in california but when it does he covers the nuvi in a plastic sandwich bag", "i received a nuvi as a gift and was impressed with its performance in the car but as a competitive <OOV> category 2 i was intrigued at the possibility of <OOV> a wired computer for my new road bike the nuvi has a screen that displays all of the pertinent information speed moving time total time max speed ave speed etc and a battery that will carry me through my longest rides 5 hours when the screen brightness is set below 30 so i decided to see what types of bike mounts were available and despite the expense of garmin's", "perfect fit it's been on here for over a year thru bumpy rides and all one of the best additions i've ever put on my bike"]

column6: ["i agree with the above reviewer <OOV> for the most part with the exception of his statement that the product does what the description says it does what the amazon description says but the of apple's av cables which work fine on their own all that can be said about this dock as far as video is concerned is that", 'we have been using this for quite some time and are happy with its performance no problems with its form or function', 'managed to connect my ipod nano 5th generation with rca cable i had lying to my old stereo <OOV> sound my stereo produced when connecting the ipod directly via the rca cable was <OOV> i puchased the apple docking station and it works sound is a lot better <OOV> is a bit expensive though especially when taking into consideration that your ipod is not recharging as i had expected but to throw more money at it for that it is getting too expensive but more importantly the remote control has a menu botton and it turns out that the menu', "as with other reveiws one wonders why apple would produce a remote control with buttons without corresponding functions while the product charges the ipod iphone and provides analog connections it lacks the s video connection of the previous apple dock the s video worked fine with ipods older than the itouch version and looked better than the headphone jack connectors now sold by apple it seems odd that apple would go backwards with a product however it's consistent with the company's goal of seeking more profit for less all in all i would not pay full retail but it's okay", "i own 2 ipods a 5th generation 60gb and an ipod classic 60gb i've just bought an apple universal dock with remote and the original apple component and composite av cables i connected the universal dock to my tv via the composite cable with my ipod 5th gen i can watch videos on the tv and control the ipod with the apple remote but when i connect my ipod classic to the universal dock it will charge but i can't get any video out or control the ipod with the remote it's as if the ipod classic doesn't recognize the", "it's easy to overlook but this dock does not include any cables and has some specific requirements column6: ['this product has already proven its worth by surviving a bad fall and i still have all the data for my phd <OOV>', "overall the hard drive is great i'm not so impressed with the design but then again it was made ruggedized so i can't complain the transfer speeds are not optimal but for a 5400rpm drive it still clips along at a pretty good pace expect a good amount of waiting time to transfer large amounts of data i e folders of documents music videos that are around 10 20 gb in size however as long as you have the time to spare it's worth it because this drive is reliable i have not had any errors or hardware malfunctions with", "i'm impressed with lacie's rugged drive it does take more punishment than a normal casing speed was not bad either", "the hard casing and rubber lining on the hard drive is great for travel you can also buy a extra external case for extra protection if you wish it has great write speed doesn't need an external power source and with 500 gb is able to back up everything needed for everyday use i recommend when you first plug it in to go through the setup wizard really helps and all you get is one chance so if you don't the first time you don't at all", "as a pro photographer i have bought a lot of hard drives and this one is by far superior 1 super durable i traveled for 2 weeks shooting in <OOV> and never had to worry about bumpy travel and wear and tear 2 super small doesn't take up too much space in my gear backpack 3 powered by usb i don't need an outlet to make it run so as long as i have battery power in my laptop i can upload photos to it great for times where there's no power outlets chase <OOV> and many other pro <OOV>", "i backed up nearly 100gb from my macbook pro to the lacie my first effort had the lacie unexpectedly quit on me after one hour my second effort completed the job in two hours that's fine next day i worked on some files and loaded some images into my computer i wanted the lacie to backup the new file versions and additional images the software only allows you to backup your entire hard drive you can't simply update a modified file or two i went to the lacie website and downloaded a free assistant called <OOV> backup assistant it flat", "i've bought two of these in the last year both are working perfectly absolutely no problems i'd buy another one now if i needed it", 'i have several lacie external hard drives and very satisfied with all of them this drive i would say is great for portability the only thing to keep in mind is that you need two usb ports to use it because this does not have a power adapter']

column6: ["i bought three of these drives to use for backups for macs opened one hooked it up to an intel imac os x 10 4 11 via firewire and nothing appeared on desktop disk utility didn't see it system profiler couldn't even identify the firewire device though it saw something on the firewire bus i powered it off tried the usb port and it doesn't even register in system profiler much less come up opened the second drive same thing nada tried using my own cables tried opening it on a ppc mini a g4 laptop all running 10 4", "my experience with this unit is mixed and this review replaces the one star rating i gave it a month ago hopefully this will offer some clarity to my experience with it april 20 2008 one <OOV> drive arrived doa it powered up but was not read by either my pc or my mac because it wasn't read i couldn't use a disc utility to partition or reformat the drive i had a major project that needed a 1tb external drive and this doa unit really killed my deadline i had to send it back to wd for a warranty", 'i just purchased this drive from costco for my apple imac 24 inch 2008 model it would not connect or be recognized when i tried the firewire 400 method the drive did not even show up on my desktop i then tried using usb2 and it connected up no problem i then reformatted the drive for mac and it seemed to work fine with usb2 i really bought this since it had a firewire 400 connection so i tried everything to get it to work including making sure i had the latest software upgrade for the drive from the wd', 'i have have 500 gb model running on osx 10 5 with no issues the 1 tb model is problematic with quality i have already returned 5 drives for various issues does not spin up 2x spins up but not recognized 2x and doa did <OOV> says with tech support swap cables connected to diff cpu diff os vista xp osx diff interfaces swapped out with existing wd my book drive 500 gb model uninstalled and reinstalled drivers if you still want to try it make sure you can return it because you probably will', 'i have had the drive 2 months now i use 3 partitions one for mac timemachine backup one for win xp backup and one for imovie video files i have had no problems my backups are done by firewire 400 and run without a hitch the xp backup uses the software that came with the drive this software will find your essential files and back them up its easy to add additional directories to back up the one thing i did not like is that it backed up all image files on the drive you end up with images from', "i have this drive for some time now as people did the first days i had problems with the drive not spinning up it would work perfect one time then just sleep the next it would not boot with the computer although i hear the spinning sound that's difficult as the drive's really quiet after thinking of returning it the first day i decided to look at the causes i have never had good experience with customer services so i decided to go for it myself the problem turned out to be the usb cable given with the drive the", "bought the drive transferred my files 1 week later it won't spin up any longer the data is irreplaceable it was my backup as the original files were on failing drives called western digital sounds like you have a bad power supply we'll send you out a new one ok didn't work called back we have a data recovery service that you can use so let me see if i understand this correctly you produce a shotty drive and then when you've got your customers by their you know whats you hook them into a data recovery service nice so", "this is an outstanding product and i'm very glad i bought it installation for a mac is a breeze and it works just as advertised warranty registration is a snap and the western digital pages have good tech info and faqs i even like the automatic backup utility they include it's easy to set up and works the first backup takes hours i <OOV> files folders with 200 gigs or so of data but incremental backups are fairly fast i prefer to use it when i'm not using other computer resources or applications since it slows them down a bit"]

column6: ["this is a pretty nifty gadget the eee pc i have got it a few days ago and had the chance to fool around with it for a while it's an excellent product for what it is a cheap <OOV> laptop the closest competitor of this caliber or at least this size easily jump above and beyond 1 grand from that alone it's a standout and in a class of its own i have not had a chance to play with the operating system it came with i had a tweaked copy of windows xp as soon as i received", "if you think you'd rather spend an extra 100 and get a real laptop think about how often you carry around an 8 pound 15 screen laptop and what you actually use the laptop for the eee pc is 2 pounds and the size of a portable 7 dvd player and chances are it will do everything that you would do with a regular laptop also the ac adapter for the eee is the size of a cellphone nokia charger not a brick and ask yourself how often do you carry your regular laptop without a charger so the size", "nicely built except 3 inherent flaws display keyboard storage the 7 lcd at <OOV> is really a nightmare for productivity given its windows like gui granted it's larger than some smartphone displays but browsing or using spreadsheets on the <OOV> display which despite its nice color and sharpness is not something you want to do for long the os gui is a mimic of windows xp from cosmetics down to the shortcut keys i might add not optimized at all for the low resolution built in display you'll want at least 1280x1024 for all the space consuming menus and <OOV>", "using my asus 701 to write this review i must say i am very happy with this purchase it's very fast for what it's intended purpose is i love the boot time is beyond the speed i was expecting this is perfect for quickly checking email bank accounts etc without the lag time of windows to boot i've viewed some graphic rich sites and it handles them like a pro even has a built in web cam which you have to see to believe the audio is ok but i use a pair of battery powered speakers and it makes", "this computer really meets my needs i needed something that was easy to travel with that i could take notes on and have a place to dump my audio and picture files it doesn't do everything but it does a lot because this little pc fit inside my pocketbook that's all i had to take on the plane instead of taking a carry on bag with cds and other entertainment all my music easily fit on the computer with plenty of room to spare it was so nice to be able to just whip out the computer from my bag", "whether or not this is the machine for you will depend on your needs in my case i use my laptop almost exclusively for writing and the internet and i carry it around with me all over the world my old 6 pound laptop was really taking its toll column6: ['i purchased this splitter since i was starting to have trouble with my cable modem i normally do not buy monster products since i think they are over priced but i do believe that they make tried a 900mhz 2 way splitter i was still having problems so i decided to try this splitter the problem i was having is that', "i'm using this to split my comcast signal to a dvr and my wireless gateway when i test the wireless speeds on my laptop i get 30mbps or over which is exactly what my subscription is the splitter itself is made with quality materials and seems it will hold up for a long time", 'really improved the picture quality on all my tvs the product does the same job as an amplified signal booster at 1 3 of the cost lovely', "well all in all it seems to be working fine i've had problems before with the cheaper brands so i thought i would buy better quality this time around", 'i used this splitter for my small project this is working excellent i am recommending this excellent product to others', "i have a voip phone connected to a router on an internet connection that was split with the cable tv the problem was that my phone wasn't working properly my voice kept cutting out to the person i was talking to after determining the problem was with my internet connection it was further determined that the phone worked fine when i removed the splitter that i had took the tv out of the mix and plugged the internet connection directly into the jack in the wall so the problem was either going to be with the splitter or there just", 'this product works much better than other monster name brand splitters depending upon your configuration it should help you as well', "i'm no techie so i won't bother on to that end as a layman full time mommy i decided to try to fix the fuzzy screen problem on our loft kids playroom tv ordered it overnight plugged it into our tv and a fresh line of cable fresh hdmi cable and split it to the cable modem results faster internet and much better picture quality not perfect but 10x better could have been the cables but i'm guessing it's this little gem 5 stars if you've got picture issues and an old splitter give it a chance"]

column6: ["update 05 31 2012 this little box still rocks alternately powering up one of either two pairs of headphones or a set of desktop speakers for the last 3 years the only very minor problem i've ever had with this device over all this time is the same problem all volume sliders and knobs have had throughout electronics history the metal contacts inside the sliders <OOV> over time and don't make contact as well as they should sometimes causing a bit of static when you move them or when it's just being temperamental the glitch only happens extremely seldom maybe", 'i live in a townhouse so there are times when i can not turn up my stereo this is the perfect alternative with a good set of headphones you can listen as loud as you wish without disturbing the neighbors', "works fine plenty loud very happy with purchase would recommend this to many people but don't but it all the way up", 'i found this product after <OOV> buying a sony lcd hdtv with no headphone output installation was very easy rca cables in and mini headphone out volume and sound quality of unit are more than adequate for this application this unit received four stars only due to somewhat high cost very nice unit', "i tried to wait a couple of days to write this review of the unbelievable rolls <OOV> <OOV> pro headphone amp which the manufacturer's insert touts as being for school studio broadcast anywhere you need four channels of clean loud headphone <OOV> man i'll second that how about your very own home photography pc mac studio does that qualify dear rolls people i think so anyway the sound and output is so compelling and incredible that i couldn't wait to publish this <OOV> like the other very nice review above this one ie the 1st one by the gentleman from", "i just column6: ["i bought this armband both for the reviews and for the look feel unfortunately it was 20 i should have just thrown out i did like the feature of being able to use the attachment to tie up my earphone cable however that was the only positive you can't use your ipod nike attachment with this armband as it covers the entire bottom of the ipod except for the hole to put in the earbuds it was extremely hard to change a song even to just push forward and finally it fell apart in a month just tore along 2", "i read the reviews and was a little skeptical about the latching system but took a chance and ordered it it does take a while to get used to but once i got the hang of it i prefer it to the typical velcro systems on other bands it holds tighter and is less bulky i really like the clip that holds the cord for the ear buds also as an avid runner i highly recommend this ipod armband i've had several different ones over the years and this is by far my favorite", "the armband in addition to having no elasticity <OOV> up all moisture that it comes <OOV> contact with the back of the ipod compartment is the same material and has no lining this allowed sweat and moisture into my ipod which fried the screen and corroded the circuitry i wish someone had mentioned this in a review before ii purchased this if it were possible i'd demand that belkin replace the ipod their armband destroyed", 'all the features are good with the exception of the hook that secures the closure on the band it is difficult to manipulate the hook into the right slot with one hand velcro would have been an easier way to close the band around my arm', 'outstanding product designed to allow owners of 3rd generation i pod to wear their i pod on their arm great quality', 'it is very handy you can put your earphones in the small case provided and the material is perfect', 'i use the armband everyday the adjust ability makes it very comfortable and easy to use i loved the price the clip for holding the headphone cord works well to keep the cord from getting in the way and has been invaluable the case that came with it helps protect my ipod when it is plugged into my car stereo and has undoubtedly saved the ipod from damage it also makes for worry free transport in my pocket or my satchel', 'i found the strap method difficult to use getting the metal hanger into the foam slot i column6: ["this was ordered to replace my mother in law's ac adapter and she could not be happier with it she is in her mid 70's and her laptop is her window to the world so she was worried about her she was delighted and happy she could plug back into her online world", 'the unit appears adequate and performs the functions for which it is designed no problems with function or installation item was purchased to power up a laptop adapter and is working as required', "buy it other reviews say its faulty or isn't the same as dell oem they're right on one point it is a third party manufactured device but it works i've had mine for over a year now and it works very well it gets hot when its charging and that is expected match the correct charger for your <OOV> just a few <OOV> difference can cause your touchpad to malfunction or other weird things to happen this works well i would buy another if this one ever failed", "i thought my laptop was done bought this and now it works great again connection is a little loose but i haven't had any problems with it coming out during use", 'it did not work i did not return the adapter because of time crunch and the process that is involved it is still here adding to my electronics clutter', 'purchased as a replacement adapter when my original finally broke after 4 years of use after 3 days the cord began fraying from the adapter by week two it started sparking every once in a while by week 4 it shorted out and began smoking do not waste your money do not buy', 'works like it should brought the laptop back to new specs and that is what i needed to have it be', 'this is the second replacement for this part power cords and adapter the power cord keeps falling apart prior parts did not stand up the rugged wear and tear this one is lighter and covering looks solid cord is smooth and nice and pliable as it should be it arrived unexpectedly soon which was great since we had to share cords until it got here note first set from dell had imperfections in the wire covering which quickly turned into exposed wire and dell replaced second set was due to wear and tear around the end of the plug attached']

column6: ['these are computer speakers and require a usb connection and software installation to work now that your expectations are aligned let me get down to the good the bad and the ugly the good the software installation and usb connection eliminate the need for a sound card one less thing to generate heat in your system box and with the multi core processors available now there should be limited or no impact on your system speed there is an mp3 player jack on the side of the right hand speaker you provide the cable to connect you ipod etc to', "i was shocked at the quality of these speakers i got these for 80 they used to retail for 300 so i thought what the heck i'll give them a whirl i was blown away by the clarity of the speakers for watching movies listing to music playing games etc i read all the reviews before buying and the biggest complaint i was seeing is that the volume doesn't go that high i'll tell you that the volume goes very high and it is very loud at max volume if you are using these for pc speakers let's be serious", "i'll start off by saying that even though my review of these speakers is pretty critical i don't think they're awful although they're not good either if i had to do it over again i would pass on these speakers i didn't buy from amazon and they're pretty heavy so i'd take such a hit returning them or <OOV> them that i found a way to live with the faults probably my biggest problem with these speakers is that they suffer from a common problem cheap speaker syndrome speaker manufacturers tend to <OOV> the bass to make up for lack", 'i have had these speakers for about 3 years now and logitech never fixed the problem i actually stored them in the basement for 2 years because the problem was so frustrating and now i revived them but to no avail i originally had vista <OOV> and the speakers would suddenly stop working after 1 to 3 hours of operation i now have windows 7 <OOV> and have the same problem the only way to fix it is to reboot i searched everywhere and hundreds of people on the internet have the same problem with no other solution they sound', "the logitech z cinema surround sound system is officially designed only for windows based operating systems using windows media center in this age of computer versatility logitech does not provide any support for macs the good news is that these speakers can indeed work on a mac despite the specification requirements of windows xp or vista and the sound is awesome as long as you aren't doing anything else on the computer while this system does not create true surround sound more satellite speakers are needed they have the power to simulate it you won't hear the explosion behind you", 'in this day of advanced surround sound technology it seems to be getting impossible to find a good computer sound system that does not include rear speakers which are often difficult if not impossible to install and never have cables that are long enough even for a small room there are a variety of systems now with wireless rear speakers but most do not seem to get very good ratings for sound quality and reliability so hard to justify the expense i could not but help column6: ["do not buy this changer i have had two of these and two of its predecessor the <OOV> non hdmi <OOV> it seems that sony just can't make a dvd player worth owning any more it has all the features i want including the <OOV> hdmi excellent image and audio output and logical controls the problem is that it's a piece of junk tonight i just boxed up my newest version bought 3 5 months ago to send back to sony for exchange 33 00 plus tax since it just stopped playing dvds entirely i have had similar problems with", 'this is a great upscale dvd player i brought this one to replace my previous model which only upscaled to 1080i and was pleasently surprised at the picture quality it is easy to hook up and operate and looks stylish looking for an upscale changer this is the one', "a great player it replaced an older sony 5 disc changer that wouldn't read cd rs it works much like the older unit has the same dimensions and has better resolution from an enhanced laser lens the only problem and others have mentioned it is a slow load time and slow read write you can get used to it but coming from an older generation of sony dvd players it's a step backward the remote is also less versatile than the older one but perhaps a bit simpler to operate the unit is built in malaysia instead of korea or", "as with all sony products it is overpriced it works just fine and i recommend it to be honest i have all sony equipment and i have never had an problem with any of them not to say they don't fail they do i am retired from electronics service so i know", "bought this dvd player to replace our old multi cd player not only does this player play dvd's it also plays cd's and mp3's recorded onto <OOV> or <OOV> with room for 5 dvd's you can play over 7000 mp3 songs nice substitute for a <OOV> box so easy to use i bought a second one for my mother in law and even she loves it pros compatibility with all standard dvd's and cd's excellent price for what you get ability to play all mp3 recorded disks hdmi ease of hookup cons the labels for the disk locations are hard", "i needed a <OOV> changer for another room this changer will not get much us i chose sony over other brands because their multi disc players always worked for me you can change a disc out while another one is playing i do not have this hooked up to high audio video connections just with the cords out the of the box my tv is about 6 years old and not an hdtv i'm happy with the sound and picture quality i don't know how it would do on my hdtv with sound system if you are looking for an", "this is a very good player i've had no problems at all with it so far which is more than i can say for the last to dvd players i've purchased rca models this time i wanted sony because my sony dvd writer has been an outstanding performer i was please but not surprised to find that they did a great job on this one too the only thing i've found about it that i don't like is that on the tray the disk numbers are stamped into the black plastic so you cannot read them without really good lighting", "just adding my bad experience to the growing number of complaints being listed here re sony dvp <OOV> b hdmi cd progressive scan 5 disc dvd player aside from having an extremely frustrating remote it began having intermittent problems about 7 months in increasing gradually to failure just after 1 yr warranty expired had an old 5 disc carousel magnavox that lasted almost 9 years wish there was a company that would make products that aren't disposable there are more of these electronics in the trash piles than in homes will never buy another sony product after this experience"]

column6: ['i see no problems with this product i put them on my quad months ago they work just fine as some other posts have claimed that they didnt stay tight i havent had that problem at all', 'these mirrors are not the highest quality things around but they are worth the money they are convex so they have a wider field of view than the factory mirrors on my <OOV> it is very nice that i am not looking at my shoulders when i look in the mirrors now they can be a little difficult to get tightened up in the handle bars instead of using rubber expansion joints to mount inside the bars they use aluminum sleeves i had to fight with one of them for about 10 minutes to get it to tighten up also', "i purchased these for my boyfriends <OOV> yamaha 750 i was a bit sceptical due to the price and and size of the mirrors but these are great they don't vibrate at all and are perfectly clear when he first went to install them they fell right out of my handle bars when he <OOV> them all the way down it was a very simple fix though all he had to do was line up the cuts in the two expanding sleeves with each other take the tapered piece that the bolt threads into and tap it into the sleeves", 'its like a whole new world being able to see everything behind me i dont know how they will hold up but it seems like they will last', "i can't believe that these have a 4 star rating sure they look decent for the money but its all downhill from there i tried installing these on a standard 7 8 inch bar i didn't have a torque wrench but they were still loose after significantly tightening the mounting bolt it was too the point that i was sure it would cause damage to go further i considered giving up here but decided that i would at least see how they look while seated on the bike after adjusting the mirror i began tightening the clamp bolt just to", 'awesome', 'cheap and easy to install not a lot of vibration mirrors are a bit small but they do the job good mirrors if your on a low budget good buy', 'these are great little mirrors i love the concave glass for better visibility and the multiple adjustment points makes positioning them very easy the only thing i found <OOV> was the bar end mounting pieces had to be stretched out or opened up to make them fit on my initial attempt to install them the allen key just spun and did not tighten after using some pliers and opening up the <OOV> inside the mount it fit better and then tightened with no problem over all it took maybe 10 <OOV> to install had i not had to take my']

column6: ['for the money this is a great product i also have a 1g nano and this product works very well on this speaker it fits without any modification and all the functions work i am very please with this travel speaker', "i'm 100 happy with the creative <OOV> <OOV> it work perfect and it <OOV> as it was in the new box thank you verry much", "best thing to take if u want to listen to your ipod anywhere living in fl your always outside when its nice it's loud enough to hear it at the beach pool on the boat it's a great product", "i see the price changes often on this speaker i paid about 19 which was a good value of course the sound from this speaker isn't as good as what you would get from a larger system but it does very well without much tinny sound it is a great portable speaker especially for listening to audiobooks i also really like that i can put it in the base to listen to recharge the speaker or to recharge my ipod", 'this is exactly what i was looking for it is tiny but has big sound i like that it uses a rechargable battery has a power cord i looked at several other portable speakers that only used alkaline batteries hate the thought of going through batteries all the time also this charges your ipod at the same time when its plugged in now i can have my music wherever i am without using my earbuds all the time love it', "in the box docking station adjustable stand rechargeable adapter it does not come with a usb cable size test when you put the latest ipod nano third generation short one with rounded corners with the <OOV> <OOV> and you get a speaker about the size of a classic ipod it passes the portability test lightweight and not bulky sound test i don't <OOV> to be a pro when it comes to sound bass and <OOV> so i couldn't evaluate the product at that level of detail from what my family and i hear we think the speaker provides good sound", "for the money you pay for this thing you could get a much better sounding ipod speaker however that speaker wouldn't be portable or have an internal battery i guess it depends on what you want i'm a teacher and i like this thing since i can easily lock it in my desk at the end of the day a larger unit could be easily stolen also i can bring it with me to different classes to play background music as students work you really can't play this thing at high volumes it gets too distorted for jazz based music", "i like this speaker it's much easier to use this than to use computer speakers which is what i used to have to use if i wanted to share my ipod music with others it's also great for watching videos not only is it easier for me to hold onto this device than to grip a tiny 3rd gen ipod nano but i can also place this speaker in its included plastic stand and be totally hands free while watching videos the sound quality isn't phenomenal but neither is an ipod's and you can't expect awesome sound quality out of"]

column6: ["this charger is exactly what i've been looking for i'm a college student and i use my iphone nonstop i used to have trouble sometimes because i would have to ration my useage incase the batter would run out by the end of the day if say i listened to a few hours of music browsed the net a little and talked on the phone for an hour id have to find a plug point and always remember to bring my charger or go back home but with this batter it's been very convenient i just pop it in my", "i think this product is sufficient for use in the short term but obviously would not be a substitute for a direct charge by ac i like that it's available and that i can use it when necessary it is great to have as a backup in case the battery on my iphone is low it's also small enough not to be bulky and difficult to carry", "i really wanted to like this item as it's a backup charger that's small enough to fit in your pocket but i've found the connection is really lose on every compatible iphone i've tried it on for those that have this same problem here's a quick tip if you set the battery extender and charger on the floor standing up and then set your phone on it the weight of the phone fixes the connection issue if you're looking for a backup charger i'd try something else", 'i recieved one kensington battery as a present and initially liked it so much i puchased a second after less the 10 charges one unit stopped accepting a change the second is taking longer to charge then i would have expected buyer beware do expect this device to last', 'this battery has saved me so many times it is worth having i would recommend it to anyone great price also', 'ok i was really excited to get this charger it looked cool and had good reviews it does work great i will give it that my only oversight that i am wanting others to be aware of is for the 1st generation ipod touch the headphone jack is located on the bottom right of the ipod when you plug this thing in it completely covers up the headphone jack so if you are watching a cool movie and your battery runs low you have to stop and wait for it to charge tip if you are traveling keep it attached', 'i adore this battery it is small enough to slide into the pocket of my small purse to go with me everywhere it easily fits on my iphone 3g while the phone is inside its crystal jacket i also like the way it charges up the iphone instead of simply providing power so that you can use your iphone while the battery is charging it pop the battery off to recharge it and use your now fully charged iphone while the battery is being charged you never have to wait if my kensington mini battery ever dies i would definitely', 'if you have an apple iphone 3g then you probably have the same three complaints that everyone else does 1 no video <OOV> no <OOV> battery life is <OOV> the kensington mini battery extender helps address the third flaw i also bought an incase power slider because i was wondering how they compared i had read reviews and heard from people that the mophie juice pack had problems with the rubber case falling off so i decided to skip that one although i played around with it a bit before buying the incase all these products perform their basic function']

column6: ["the grip came sooner than promised this item is actually reviewed on a lot of professional sites i had no problem looking it up before i purchased it they all gave it very high marks and i can see why this item is a very good piece for this price it doesn't look cheap and it is fully functional for extending battery life and as a vertical grip it integrates into my wifes xti perfectly and she loves it i would say that this is as close to a perfect item as can be once price <OOV> and function are", "i wasn't sure what to expect when i purchased this for my canon xt i bought it as a battery backup for those occasions when i drain my other batteries i have used it both with the canon camera battery and with the six aa battery magazine i can sum up my feelings for this unit in two words love it yes there are some downsides but overall i love using the grip the downsides the magazines sometimes are tricky to get to line up perfectly in order to close the battery compartment i have been impressed with the battery", "excelent price 2 batteries extended shooting time grip extension makes camera more comfortable to hold don't wait buy now", 'it fits perfectly on my camera canon eos rebel xti 400d and works as canon gear double your cameras shutter capacity so you can shoot all day long in case you run out of batteries it has an adapter to use aa batteries', "i can't imagine a better grip even if made by the manufacturer the feel of the grip and the controls are just like those on the camera itself adds weight balance i got this on amazon for less than 40 at that price don't even think buy it worth much more", 'other makers charge way to much for this item been using for a few days now and im very pleased matches the texture and look of camera has worked flawless up till now', 'at first i was thrilled with this grip it is a huge asset for the xti especially for people with large hands the controls on the grip all are easy to use and while they do not have the same feel as the built in controls it is not difficult to get used to them in particular the shutter button is softer than the build in one it is slightly heavy but the added comfort of the larger grip more than make up for it these things considered for the price it would be a 5 star review however after', 'wow this is awesome i bought it for my rebel xt and decided to pass on the more expensive canon version it works great and was easy to attach to the camera it just feels great in your hands the rubber gives you a better grip and the overall added weight and size make the camera easier to hold i also love the added buttons for shooting portraits this product is really a great deal']

column6: ['works great out of the box on my vista pc unlike some previous generations of entry level drives from kingston this one can be used with windows readyboost to enhance system performance which means that the drive satisfies some minimum read write speed requirement i like the swivel cap design it protects the usb plug well without a loose cap to worry about misplacing', "would be 5 stars with a clip key chain or something to hang onto so small i'm afraid i'm going to lose it", "i needed a new thumb drive and saw that this particular one had good reviews when it arrived i plugged it into the computer and it worked fine until the next time i used it no computer will recognize it it doesn't show up at all i tried kingston's troubleshooting and nothing resolved the issue i had the thumb drive for all of 3 days i've never had an issue like that with a thumb drive before i will not be buying another one i requested a refund rather than a replacement i'll be getting a sandisk instead", 'integral cover is nice it would be nice if you could rename it on you computer when you use other kingston drives', "can't go wrong for the price works fast and feels solidly built like everyone else said it would be nice for the cover to lock in place but that's not a deal breaker", 'about 10x faster than cd rw by my estimate from what i hear flash memory is very reliable too this device is true plug play just plug it into to the usb port and the drive is instantly recognized by windows no drive formatting required either', 'own several and this with <OOV> protector looks to be even better rec to all for portability ease of use as well as very reasonable cost factor', 'i bought this kingston flash memory because a at t tech recommended i get a flash memory i chose kingston because of the gb and the price two days after i received it i had to reformat my computer plugged the little thingy in and selected my pictures and files i wanted to save and kingston saved them all i have had to reformat my computer before and lost everything after i reformatted my computer i plugged in my little kingston flash memory and downloaded everything back on my computer great little product good price and very easy to use']

column6: ["first off there are no options to request freeway usage preference only to avoid freeways and for some reason nuvi thinks it is faster to not take freeways even in no traffic and a 20 mi drive i've had several instances where it had me turn off the main road only to turn back onto it a mile later maybe this would be worth it if you were avoiding a terrible traffic signal but even then making 2 left turns on a major street takes as much time or more than sitting through a red light it is very difficult", 'when i read the spec sheet on this garmin it said that this gps would guide me down route 66 all it did was get me to route 66 in chicago when i left chicago i selected the 1st leg of the trip and all this gps did for the entire 20 days that i was riding route 66 was try to point me back out to the interstate it would actually show that i was riding on route 66 but would try to route me out to the interstate should have save the money to pay for gas i', "i've used my nuvi 500 for <OOV> with ram mount geocaching and in the car it's been on the bike in driving rain without problem the bad only car charging cable included a standard inexpensive usb cable will transfer data with a computer but won't charge the unit lack of magnetic compass hurts geocaching capabilities no headphone jack maps don't differentiate between a good gravel road and a dirt path that requires <OOV> and a <OOV> poi's are missing many long standing <OOV> even after doing all the auto updates mine still doesn't speak street names where's the manual the", 'good gps but not what i expected screen is small and moving to different sections of the map is difficult as i said good but i expected more', "i would've given it 5 stars if it only had a way to carry it with a lanyard there is no place to attach any strap besides that it does a great job thru traffic and geocaching", "it works great and i haven't got lost yet so in 11 more words i will say it was worth it", "background late in 2008 i decided to buy a gps unit for a cross country tour with the motorcycle total miles 4800 determined with google <OOV> on reviews and specs i decided to go for the nuvi 500 features i required waterproof yes <OOV> <OOV> life about 5 6 hrs in real life degraded over time to 3 <OOV> osx interface yes via roadtrip however garmin hasn't updated roadtrip since 03 24 <OOV> favorites yes up to <OOV> up to <OOV> satellite reception slow takes quite some time to acquire <OOV> i would have liked in addition faster satellite reception", '<OOV> 500 dd not come packaged with computer cord had to order on line as no local vender for the cord maps would not down load and was on line for 45 <OOV> tech i bought it for the topo potential i <OOV> had a magellan cross over that worked very <OOV> difficult to get a live garman rep on the phone 15 to 20 minute <OOV>']

'the hard drive dead several month after purchasing would never buy anything from this brand and will tell friends about it the appearance is rough not very well polished', "i bought mine 500gb on october 21 2009 the first thing i did was delete all the preloaded software so i can't comment on that and then i partitioned the drive used truecrypt to encrypt one of the partitions and then started transferring files maybe i just take better care of my <OOV> or pay closer attention to what i'm doing when connecting disconnecting traveling handling etc but in the 2 5 years i've been transporting this hd back forth from work every work day i've never experienced any of the problems others have reported it has been rock solid", "this is the 2nd iomega drive i have purchased the first one just stopped working copying for no reason it worked fine for a week i did not drop it or miss use it i returned it purchased the iomega prestige portable series i have had it now about a month now from day one the usb connector was weak would disconnect with out barley touching it now it won't connect at all 2 bad drives in a row i either have bad luck or they are just garbage", 'i just loved the size of this hard drive we use it with one of the mini <OOV> so it just fit have not had any problems with it love it so far', 'my laptop had so much music and pictures on it that there was not enough remaining memory for it to function this external hard drive allowed me to free up space so that i can enjoy my laptop again and it was easy enough to install for a novice like myself i am quite pleased', "i just got a 500gb prestige i plugged it in with one of the y usb's and the dell would not recognize the drive after reviewing the manual that came with it the <OOV> was to plug in both usb's this corrected the problem and now it can see the drive after <OOV> through a bunch of reviews for the prestige wd passport and other brands of drives apparently this power issue is not <OOV> to just this iomega product but occurs across brands clearly the manufacturer does not advertise this 2 usb port thing as a feature so it", "its a pretty good hard drive i use it for all my important files and pictures of my kids it's good to know something out here works and they're making even better"]

camera helps alot and also try to push back the tension spring bar thing across the back of the inside of the film compartment to help prevent the film leader ripping off as these film packs are <OOV> slightly larger than the originals polaroid made", 'film was well within date code and arrived in good condition this film works great in polaroid land film cameras like the 100 250 etc with 3000 speed it is much easier to take pictures in low light levels than with the fp 100 and it has a faster development time very sharp high contrast film', "this was the first film i tried with my polaroid <OOV> the first picture came out beautifully indoor shot then i took some outdoor shots and got huge white blotches on most of the shots the following indoor shots were too dark and the final three shots no matter where i took were nothing but white i made sure to load the film in subdued light and i cleaned the rollers i'm now trying the equivalent colour pack in the camera and am getting beautiful results so i'd be wary of buying the b w again", "i use a canon 1dx and <OOV> with l glass but when it comes to shooting a photograph that subjects will admire for it's instant physical whether we are shooting a fashion <OOV> with fill flash in a cold nyc times square or a situation under mixed indoor low light <OOV> shines fuji <OOV> is the last of the black and white peal apart style films as", "this is the only instant b w film left on the market it's the intended film for the polaroid <OOV> 100 400 series <OOV> and other cameras that can use it the whole purpose to the battery i put it in a box and amazon paid the shipping to returned it', "what's not too love bought this for my sis in law as a gift and she went from half an hour on her original and quite aged battery to over six everybody's happy and if you buy this you will be too", 'i am so happy with this battery it fit easily in my computer is the same size as the original battery and has great life my old battery was only lasting an hour or so but this new one is lasting 4 5 6 hours depending on use very happy', 'this gave my netbook a real boost by having up to five hours of normal battery capability i do email and web searches but no streaming video in that time in other words normal computing', 'i ordered this battery for an asus eeepc 1000h it fit my netbook very tightly it was tight enough to require some care to get it fully seated but it did slide into place without any serious difficulty according to my netbook software ubuntu linux the battery holds slightly more than its rated capacity and my informal observations are that it lasts over 4 hours with no power saving changes applied to my system the color is dark gray near black and does not match the case color finish of my asus perfectly though this is not important to me', "i can't complain about the fit or the performance but it has a drastically different shape than the one that came with my asus <OOV> despite being rated at the same <OOV> mah the rear of my netbook now sits up about 3 4 inch higher than before it's like the computer is on some sort of stand i'm not sure why this is necessary since it has the same capacity as the factory battery at present there are two pictures here at amazon the official one makes the battery look the same size as my asus battery the other", "so far so good it seems to hold a comparable charge to oem on my 1000h good build and fit good charge good price wish they'd make one for my macbook pro"]

column6: ['this product really improves the sound of our newly purchased 60 lcd tv without all of the speakers and mess of a home theatre system', 'if i could give this speaker 4 5 stars i would it is a very well made piece of equipment and absolutely simple to set up and use music sounds really good through this you would be challenged to spend 300 for a receiver and speakers that sound as good it is a major upgrade over built in tv speakers it has solid bass that you will even hear at low levels voices are very clear and natural sounding you definitely get a <OOV> soundstage with this speaker and you would think that you are listening to 3 speakers left', "upon plugging in the system it didn't power up left it plugged in and it finally turned on after about 45 minutes then came the snap crackle pop of the speakers even without an audio signal being sent to the system turned on the tv and after about 30 minutes the main speakers failed and the only sound that was heard was a muffled sub woofer i do not recommend anyone try this product garbage garbage garbage", 'this is by far the best sounding easiest to set up all in one theater system i have owned or heard bar none i have owned many 5 1 systems and also two different soundbar systems the highly rated sony ht ct 100 being one of them and the zvox 325 is the best bang for the buck crystal clear vocals smooth bass and the phase cue option is great for action movies wanted and matrix blu ray sounded amazing although music sounds much better with the phase cue turned almost all the way off while the ct 100 worked', 'i love this speaker wonderful bass and surround sound i get several positive comments about it its also fun playing games on the ps3 with the sound', "i bought the zvox 325 for my kids tv room where we often play rock band it is freaking awesome and well worth considering i was nervous it would not have enough bass like a couple of sound bars i had tried but no worries there the bass is deep and powerful this was the first speaker system i ever bought without listening to it first so was skeptical it is nice to finally buy a piece of electronics that is affordable and lives up to it's hype", "i installed the box about 3 days ago it was very easy to install and we love it my husband has a slight hearing problem and this has really helped him you don't even have to turn up real loud to get all the background voices and the sound is very crisp and clear highly recommend this system to someone that does not want wires and boxes all over your listening and viewing area i have not been able to get my mp3 player to work thru the system yet but evidently i am doing something wrong and will figure", 'have had for a month and am truly pleased with the sound music and video quality excellent for a one piece unit whats great is that you do not need to run all those <OOV> with surround sound this unit is like the bose one piece sound system which <OOV> but no video i highly recommend']

cases you find at most retail stores are far too overpriced for the exact same product a great buy all the way", "as you may already know the case is only 3 when i first opened the package for the come with that", "my wife loves it since she can hook the waistband clip on her pants or shorts when she runs and the case also covers the whole unit except for the tuning wheel hold switch and plug areas so it offers great protection for her ipod nano's screen and finish my only concern was that the plastic clip would break off but it is holding up so far after about 2 weeks of use i think it is strong enough to hold up if you are just careful with it and don't pull it open too much", "as others have stated the wheel cutout does not line up on the 5th generation nano i'm stupid for buying this and not realizing beforehand if you buy this for the 5th gen nano you probably won't be happy", 'i am happy with my purchase especially for the price it was difficult to find a case for my ipod column6: ["my daughter loves music and audio books we have bought many inexpensive and cheaply made radios cd players for her all of which ended up in the trash we finally broke down and paid a little more money to get a reliable brand we now realize that we would have saved a bunch of money had we just bought something like this in the first place the controls are easy to use it is super cute the price is great not much more than the cheapies that we have thrown away and the sound is decent for it's size it's", "bought this for my 2 year old son it's perfect durable he presses the buttons all day long and it's still working great great purchase for the price", "this boombox is stylish and easy to operate i bought it for use with audio books for my children and the sound quality is wonderful what they didn't say in the item description is that there is no headphone jack the whole room has to listen who would think in this day and age of a boombox with no headphone capability i would have given it five stars except for that", "this was very affordable and a very cute design i wanted a portable affordable cd player to bring with me to meetings to provide background music this fits the bill perfectly it's easy to use and the cd player works great i haven't used the radio yet but i am sure i will i am very happy with this purchase", "my new radio cd player is very easy to use has decent sound and is a bit larger than i had expected because i didn't measure ahead of time i listen to a radio station that is a little hard to receive from where i live but the radio reception is weaker through my new sony than through my car radio by quite a bit the sound when i am using the cd is a bit on the muffled side especially on the high low and <OOV> sections i am still pleased with the product for the price which couldn't", "as other reviewers indicated the sound is not loud enough in addition a tiny coffee spill created a permanent stain on the plastic surface rather than being cute it actually is annoying to look at after a while but this is personal and i did not factor it in my rating i'm returning mine", "perfect just what i expected ordered this for my wife who wanted an easy to use and highly portable device the sound quality is acceptable considering that it is such a small device she uses it mainly to listen to her cd's and we have not used the radio part at all", "i bought this cd player for my 77 year old mother for christmas thought it would be easy to use and adequate for her few uses when she tried it out i was actually embarrassed by the sound quality rare to find such poor technology on the market reminiscent of a child's record player from decades ago"]

column6: ["i bought this as a birthday gift for my husband it's a great smaller sized lcd for the bedroom or office we really love it the only thing is that the picture doesn't look great out of the box and because its a newer model there wasn't much info on the tweaking websites to help calibrate it we ended up using the same settings from our larger sony xbr4 and it looks great just don't be surprised by the factory settings the only reason i gave 4 stars instead of 5", 'my bravia ceased functioning after 18 months of use i took it to a repair shop and found some of the components went bad but the repair cost would be greater than a new tv the problem was not caused by a power surge or any other likely culprit according to my electronics repairman just good old fashioned shoddy build quality i had expected more from a sony aside from that the annoying auto dark mentioned by another poster was really annoying and will not be missed stay away from sony as it is not worth the price', 'dollar for dollar this is the best 26 lcd on the market today excellent <OOV> quality', "i'm probably not the best person to review a tv set because the only other one i'm thoroughly familiar with is the 25 year old rca set that this one replaced anyhow i'm very happy with the decision the image is very crisp and clear and there are numerous input options i've managed to set up three different feeds into the tv one from the cable box one from the dvd player and one direct from an antenna all of them work well if you're used to an old fashioned tv set that you just turn on and off and", 'this tv would be perfect if they included the headphone jack the 5000 does not have one the 4000 model did have one and it was a great help for the <OOV> who are both hard of hearing and unable to remember how to use wireless headphones', "great picture meets my expectations i've had sony products in the past which influenced my choice of this unit why does this review process require a minimum number of words i am a person of few words my comments were short and sweet", "this tv is used in my study it has the following devices attached to it a dell hybrid studio pc windows vista via hdmi a <OOV> pc ubuntu 8 10 via vga aka the pc port a sony playstation 2 via composite an xbox original via composite everything works as you'd expect so far in particular the hybrid intel 965 chipset running vista is able to drive the tv over hdmi in its native <OOV> resolution the edid has the correct info this was a problem with a samsung i bought and returned likewise the <OOV> pc system also bought']

connection from receiver to tv but no signal from the cable checked all connections swapped out hdmi cables turned everything off and back on but no luck bypassed the receiver connecting the cable box signal can only be used for hdmi anything else attached to the receiver will require a separate output to the tv so in our case the wii could connect to the receiver but we would need", 'i really wanted to love this receiver it had everything i was looking for at a better price than the competition i set everything up and used it for almost 2 weeks i was a little disappointed in the sound column6: ["bought this for my son's school asus netbook and it fits like it was custom made for it highly recommended", 'i bought this laptop sleeve at the same time as my netbook it is very versatile supposed to it protects my netbook from spills nicks and dust while it bounces around in my backpack it's not a replacement for a typical laptop case it doesn't have any handles pockets or additional padding the zipper seems decent and it hasn't broken yet in a few weeks of daily use i would buy one again for 8", "there's not much to say this is a great case the quality is outstanding for the price it offers a decent amount of padding and protection the only thing that would make it better would be a zippered pocket for things like a usb mouse cable power cord etc i've seen other similar cases with a pocket and it helps when you're carrying a couple of extras with your netbook otherwise it's a great deal and if you're only carrying the netbook this is well worth the money", "i like the case it holds my asus netbook without a problem there is no where to put the charge cables or my mouse but since i carry the netbook in a bigger bag it works out fine the only problem is the column6: ["i had this cooler for a couple of months and it became unreliable it wouldn't start when plugged in the first time and then would simply quit for no apparent reason i would have to pull the power connect out of the back plug it back in and gently put the laptop back on it or it would shut off again now it appears to not be working at all i can't tell if it is the power cord or the power source plug regardless i recommend against buying it", 'i bought this chill mat a few months ago at first it worked well then after a month or so the fan on the right side started to work only intermittently i would have to jiggle the power cord or hold it in a particular place for the fan to turn on after a few more weeks the right fan completely stopped working i kept using the mat a few weeks longer until the left side stopped working as well so basically the only thing it is good for after less than a year is keeping my laptop off my', 'the first thing i noticed is that it was very loud compared to my other laptop cool pad no longer available or i would have bought another one it still works great after 4 years but it worked ok so i kept it about 4 months later one of the fans started screeching if i lifted the laptop and tapped on it the noise would stop for a while then start again by the time i got annoyed enough to buy a new one i noticed that one of the two fans had died completely it was also the <OOV>', 'this was a replacement for my old cooler pad that broke i like this one so much better i wish i had purchased it first', "i did a lot of research before settling on this cooling pad for my hp touchpad the blog i read gave it a great review and it was one of the cheaper pads i saw on the net unfortunately i got what i paid for within weeks the right fan the one underneath my hard drive quit working i also experienced the screeching noise lately it's been quiet but i finally realized it was because both fans had quit working i haven't even had it a year it's taking me 30 minutes to write this review because my laptop is", "noticable difference in temperature since i started using this chill mat works great i'm sure there are better chill mats out there but this one is right for the price the usb power is very convenient very light and perfect fit for my 15 dell no slipping when placed on my lap", 'it lasted less than a month before it stopped working and when it did work the fans barely moved its not worth it its a complete waste of money', "wow there's an amazing amount of negative reviews for this product i have not experienced total failure with this cooling pad but i've come close and perhaps the reviews are well deserved i thought i had a failure of the right fan after a very short time but i recently discovered and before i read these reviews that jiggling or manipulating the power cord that inserts into the rear of the pad can make it work as some have reported the removable power cord is the weak part of the design and it is vulnerable since it is not recessed"]
